==English==
Alternative spelling ''soda syphon''

===Etymology===
'''Soda''' water + '''[[siphon]]'''

===Noun===
'''soda siphon'''
# A stout glass bottle containing [[soda water]] under pressure, at one time found in [[bar]]s. A lever operated [[valve]] at the top is used to dispense the liquid.

===Synonyms===
*[[seltzer bottle]]